note.ab:
Gauguin was once in the possession of the following paintings by Cézanne: 
    Female nude, before 1870; 
    Mountains in Provence (near l’Estaque)
, c. 1879; 
    The avenue
, c. 1879; 
    Still life with a bowl of fruit
, c. 1879-1880, and The Château of Médan, c. 1880. See Rewald 1996, vol. 1, pp. 119-120, cat. no. 140, pp. 259-262, cat. no. 391, pp. 271-272, cat. no. 409, pp. 277-280, cat. no. 418, and pp. 292-294, cat. no. 437. It is possible that 
    The harvest
, c. 1877, was also in his possession; see letter 624, n. 6. A letter written by Gauguin to Pissarro in the summer of 1883 reveals that he had two paintings by Cézanne lined by Latouche at 34 rue Lafayette. See Correspondance Gauguin 1984, pp. 50-51, 386 (n. 115). Regarding Latouche, see letter 630, n. 10.
